                            <comment id="15423928" author="rkanter" created="Wed, 17 Aug 2016 05:38:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good idea.  Two trivial changes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&apos;s add a comment above &lt;tt&gt;GMT_TZ&lt;/tt&gt; saying why it&apos;s there (e.g. &quot;GMT is the most commonly used timezone; we can save on parsing and creating a TimeZone by creating a GMT TimeZone once&quot;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Can you update the &lt;tt&gt;JsonUtils#parseDateRfc822&lt;/tt&gt; method to also use &lt;tt&gt;GMT_TZ&lt;/tt&gt; instead of creating a new one each time?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
